sentences: Murray James Wall (born 28 September 1945, in Melbourne) is an Australian jazz double bassist.
He began playing professionally in 1962 and played with visiting musicians such as Clark Terry, Mel Torme, and Billy Eckstine.
He moved to the United States in 1979 and played with Jon Hendricks in 1981–1985, including tours of Europe and Israel.
He played with Benny Goodman in 1985–1986, and following this played as a sideman with Ken Peplowski, Marty Grosz, Keith Ingham, Frank Vignola, Chuck Wilson, and Spanky Davis.
